item.description:
And on account of Smr̥ti. Smr̥ti also declares the difference of the embodied Self
and the highest Self, viz. Bha. Gītā XVIII, 61, &lsquo;The Lord, O Arjuna, is seated in the heart of all beings, driving round by his magical power all beings (as if they were) mounted on a machine.&rsquo;
But what, it may be asked, is that so-called embodied Self different from the highest Self which is to be set aside according to the preceding Sūtras?

